8. ulna, the fore-arm from the shoulder to the wrist (ὠλένη), equal to nearly two feet. The toga would be twelve feet in breadth (breadth, not length, is intended). We do not know what the ordinary breadth of a toga was, but the ordinary loose surplice (as distinguished from the short close-fitting alb) measures seven or eight feet.
